    "analysis": "The trace-anomaly inspection for MG02 shows concentrated latency spikes around timestamp 1616562000 (end of the window) across multiple trace types (notably trace.to_dockerB2.duration_mean and trace.from_Tomcat04.duration_mean). Metric fault segmentation found two high-priority MG02 metric faults: a persistent 31-minute TCP FIN-WAIT condition spanning the whole incident window (1616560200–1616562000) and an extreme single-point disk write spike at 1616560620. Combined, traces and metrics point to MG02 as the likely problematic component (network FIN-WAIT + inter-service latency + disk write spike). However, we still need corroborating log-level evidence (connection errors, disk errors, or service errors) and precise earliest occurrence correlation between metric fault start and trace/log anomalies to declare a final root cause and exact occurrence time. Therefore we need to inspect logs and error_logs for MG02 and the directly-connected services (dockerB2, Tomcat04, dockerA1, MG01, Tomcat01, IG01, Redis02) within the incident window.",
